definition:
A man of the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.8.32; 
 son of: Mikloth (H4732); also called Shimeam at 1Ch.9.38; 
Another name of shim.ah (שִׁמְאָה "Shimeah" H8039) 
 § Shimeam = "their fame"
1) a Benjamite, son of Mikloth
1a) also 'Shimeah'
